node.title: Fire crews tackle bush fire on Karikari Peninsula in Northland
node.description: The 20-hectare fire broke out at the southern end of the Karikari Peninsula in Northland.
node.content:
["Firefighters are battling a bush fire on the Karikari Peninsula in Northland.", "", "
The fire is burning at the southern end of the Karikari Peninsula in Northland. Photo: Fire and Emergency NZ
", "The 20-hectare fire broke out in manuka at the southern end of peninsula at about 5.30am.", "Four trucks and three helicopters are working on the fire, and three more choppers are on the way.", "In a statement, Fire and Emergency District Manager Wipari Henwood said the fire was burning on conservation land and at this stage no homes or other structures were at risk.", "But strong easterly winds were forecast today and he expected crews would be on the scene all day."]
